# No AI Branding in Git Commits

**NEVER** include AI tool names, branding, advertising, or attribution in git commit messages, branch names, PR descriptions, or code comments. This applies to all AI tools without exception.

## Banned Tool Names

Do not reference any of these (or similar) in commits or trailers:

Claude, Cursor, Copilot, GitHub Copilot, ChatGPT, GPT-4, GPT-4o, OpenAI, Anthropic, Gemini, Google Gemini, Windsurf, Codeium, Tabnine, Amazon Q, CodeWhisperer, Sourcegraph Cody, Replit AI, Devin, Aider, Continue, JetBrains AI

## Banned Patterns

- Attribution phrases: "Generated by", "Created with", "Made with", "Built with", "Written by", "Authored by", "Assisted by", "Powered by", "Suggested by", "Produced by", "Refactored by", "Fixed by" followed by any AI tool name
- Git trailers: `Co-authored-by:`, `Signed-off-by:`, `Reviewed-by:`, or any trailer referencing an AI tool
- Marketing language: "AI-powered", "AI-generated", "AI-assisted", "LLM-assisted", "LLM-generated", "machine-generated"
- Emoji markers that imply AI authorship (robot emoji, sparkle emoji, brain emoji as commit prefixes)
- Any other phrasing whose purpose is to advertise or attribute work to an AI tool

## Examples

